snippet.title: The week according to Matt O'Connor Saturday 17th July 2021
snippet.description:
A pleasure as always to have Matt O'Connor ( https://www.fathers-4-justice.org/ ) back with us for our regular review of all the top news stories from the past week. 

LIVE ON ALL OUR STREAMING PLATFORMS
For all our links heartsofoak.org/find-us/

Stories covered tonight:

Woke

GB News director of programming quits after host is suspended for taking knee
https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/gb-news-director-programming-quits-24552472

'Every officer is up to speed on diversity training. Not so much ship handling': Scathing official report finds US Navy is too woke for war because of risk averse, politically correct, control-freak top brass
https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-9783807/Navy-disarray-focusing-diversity-training-warfighting-report-says.html

Toby Young tweet: To put the scale of the racist abuse the England players receive on Twitter into context, the Guardian analysed more than 585,000 tweets aimed at the players during the group stages and found 44 explicitly racist messages, 0.0075% of the total.
https://twitter.com/toadmeister/status/1414987425353510914?s=20

'Nobody should trust Wikipedia,' its co-founder warns: Larry Sanger says site has been taken over by left-wing 'volunteers' who write off sources that don't fit their agenda as fake news
https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-9793263/Nobody-trust-Wikipedia-founder-Larry-Sanger-warns.html

Amber Heard says she is both 'mom and dad' to baby girl Oonagh as she shares new photo from home... after welcoming the child three months ago via surrogate
https://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-9795663/Amber-Heard-says-mom-dad-baby-girl-Oonagh.html


Covid

World Health Organisation says China 'owes it to millions' to provide information on COVID-19 pandemic
https://www.skynews.com.au/world-news/world-health-organisation-say-china-owes-it-to-millions-to-provide-information-on-covid19-pandemic/news-story/90332178c463dc4b016e8cf7d7ae0730

'She thought they were going to arrest her': Police turn up in riot van to check 'petrified' schoolgirl, 12, is isolating
https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/she-thought-were-going-arrest-21043287

More than 1,500 NHS and care workers have died in Covid pandemic in heartbreaking toll
https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/politics/more-1500-nhs-care-workers-24536105

London hospitals' wall of silence as they refuse to say how many Covid patients are vaccinated
https://www.mylondon.news/news/south-london-news/london-hospitals-wall-silence-refuse-21003332

Spain’s top court rules pandemic lockdown ‘unconstitutional’
https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/spain-rules-pandemic-lockdown-unconstitutional-b1884038.html

Covid-19: Irish government passes indoor hospitality legislation
https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-57844854


EU and LGBT

EU launches legal action over LGBTQ+ rights in Hungary and Poland
https://www.theguardian.com/world/2021/jul/15/eu-launches-legal-action-over-lgbtq-rights-in-hungary-and-poland
